00:00:07.654 --> 00:00:14.466
Today we will make gobi aloo sabzi which is liked by almost everyone.

00:00:14.757 --> 00:00:20.050
Let's see what all ingredients are required for making gobi aloo sabzi.

00:00:20.587 --> 00:00:22.587
Cauliflower - 400 grams

00:00:23.384 --> 00:00:26.796
Potato - 250 grams (2 big size)

00:00:27.062 --> 00:00:29.150
Cumin seeds - 1/2 tsp

00:00:29.542 --> 00:00:31.787
Turmeric powder - 1/2 tsp

00:00:32.321 --> 00:00:34.719
Coriander powder - 1 tsp

00:00:35.149 --> 00:00:38.404
Red chilly powder - less then 1/4 tsp

00:00:39.051 --> 00:00:41.987
Mango powder- 1/4 tsp

00:00:42.349 --> 00:00:45.722
Salt - as per taste (1 tsp)

00:00:46.177 --> 00:00:49.526
Garam masala - less then 1/4 tsp

00:00:49.928 --> 00:00:52.468
Dry fenugreek leaves - 1 tbsp

00:00:53.011 --> 00:00:56.011
Green coriander - 1 tbsp (finely chopped)

00:00:56.370 --> 00:00:58.092
Oil - for making sabzi

00:00:58.211 --> 00:01:08.239
Floret the cauliflower and then soak it in salty lukewarm water for 5 minutes.

00:01:09.783 --> 00:01:25.115
  Add little salt in lukewarm water.Now place florets in water as this helps in cleaning the florets.

00:01:34.879 --> 00:01:39.723
Soak it for 5 minutes and then take it out.

00:01:43.409 --> 00:01:49.320
Peel the potatoes and cut them just before making sabzi.

00:01:49.839 --> 00:01:52.204
Peel them and soak in water.

00:01:55.557 --> 00:01:59.542
Now add 2 tbsp oil in the pan.

00:02:07.627 --> 00:02:14.813
When oil gets hot add asafoetida,cumin seeds.

00:02:16.341 --> 00:02:35.954
When cuminseeds turn little brown add turmeric powder,coriander powder,ginger,chilies and fenugreek leaves.

00:02:38.238 --> 00:02:43.929
Saute the masala and then add florets and potatoes into it.

00:02:45.629 --> 00:02:50.925
Also add red chilly powder and salt.

00:02:52.873 --> 00:03:03.058
Stir until potatoes and florets get coated nicely with the spices.

00:03:05.749 --> 00:03:12.372
Saute for 2-3 minutes.

00:03:19.414 --> 00:03:25.388
Now add 2-3 tbsp water into the sabzi.

00:03:25.750 --> 00:03:32.474
Cover it and cook for 5-6 minutes on low flame and then check it.

00:03:41.831 --> 00:03:44.117
Add 3 tbsp water.

00:03:47.634 --> 00:03:53.023
Cover the pan and cook sabzi on low flame for 5-6 miutes.

00:03:53.918 --> 00:03:56.204
Check after 5 minutes.

00:04:03.256 --> 00:04:11.108
Stir the sabzi nicley and check whether potatoes have become tender or not.

00:04:11.585 --> 00:04:18.222
Add 2 tbsp more water if needed.

00:04:31.364 --> 00:04:36.451
Cover the pan and cook for 5 minutes more on low flame.

00:04:37.885 --> 00:04:39.528
Check again.

00:04:45.048 --> 00:04:53.091
With help of spoon check whether potatoes have become tender or not.

00:04:53.358 --> 00:05:03.017
Don't over cook the vegetables as they can get mashed and doesn't come out tasty.

00:05:03.201 --> 00:05:06.471
Sabzi should be crispy.

00:05:06.808 --> 00:05:08.887
Sabzi is now ready.

00:05:08.969 --> 00:05:34.505
Now add mango powder,garam masala and green coriander leaves in the sabzi.

00:05:35.110 --> 00:05:44.767
Gobi aloo sabzi is ready and looks delicious.

00:05:45.947 --> 00:05:48.717
Delectable Gobi aloo sabzi is ready.

00:05:49.062 --> 00:05:54.316
We have made this sabzi with 400 grams cauliflowerand 200 grams potatoes.

00:05:54.714 --> 00:05:59.905
This much quantity of sabzi can be served to 4-5 family members.

00:06:00.282 --> 00:06:06.084
Serve gobi aloo sabzi with chapatti,parantha or naan.

